# apps/edpath-backend — Express + the LangGraph agent

- `/upload` extracts, cleans, and validates PDF text **upstream of the graph** (the graph only ever starts on good text). See `docs/reference/feature-flow.md` Part C §2 and `docs/reference/architecture.md` §4.
- Express hosts the CopilotKit Runtime (the bridge to the agent) and owns the run + `threadId`.
- This is the single Zod validation chokepoint — validate every artifact here before it leaves the backend.
- Graph/agent work (nodes, edges, interrupts, state object, reliability): read `docs/reference/agent-architecture.md`.
- Persistence is the LangGraph Postgres checkpointer only — no app tables (`docs/reference/db-schema.md`).
